Description: Fragment of an amygdaloid handle probably from a pottery transport amphora. Clay fine cream-buff. Rectangular stamp. Greek inscription.
Curator's comments: Petrie Diary 1884-5 (EES Archive XVII 47) p. 51, 9. Name Zenon. The fabric and handle shape disassociate this stamp fromn other Zenon series.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.1595)
